headline: Starbucks and the Pitfalls of Investing in Turnaround Stocks
summary: Waning confidence in Starbucks' turnaround has led to a sharp sell-off in recent months.  Starbucks’ international exposure can be an advantage, but it also makes the company more difficult to turn around.  Starbucks has taken on debt with little earnings growth to show for it.
